Kilifi county commissioner Joseph Keter yesterday released guidelines to ensure security in polling centres during party primaries.To ease security operations, no one will be allowed near the polling station after voting. Keter said people will be allowed to be 30m away from the polling centres.He spoke on Tuesday in Malindi during a meeting with religious leaders, Nyumba Kumi neighbourhood watch representatives, youth and social workers.&ldquo;Community leaders should collaborate with security officers to make sure peace prevails throughout the electioneering period," Keter said.He said police will ensure no destruction of property or loss of lives during the elections.He warned aspirants and politicians against hate speech and urged them to preach peace and unity.Jamii Thabiti regional coordinator Kennedy Kibisu told political aspirants to accept results for primaries.